=== Pronunciation ===
[[Category:Hebrew language]]
אביּהוּ   - אביּה / 'ăbîyâh  'ăbîyâhû / ab-ee-yaw', ab-ee-yaw'-hoo
=== Etymology ===

From [[אב]]  {{HH|1}} and  [[יהּ]] {{HH|3050}}; father (that is worshipper) of Jah; 
=== Proper noun ===
Abijah, the name of several Israelite men and two Israelitesses: - [[Abiah]], [[Abijah]].